sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Workbench Pod<br/>Jupyter/VSCode
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelRegistry as Model Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS gRPC/9090
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Gateway: Workflow 1: Model Development to Production

    User->>Dashboard: Access UI<br/>HTTPS, OAuth Bearer Token
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR<br/>K8s API
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Deploy StatefulSet<br/>Container: notebooks:1.42.0

    Note over Notebook: User develops model
    Notebook->>MLflow: Log experiments<br/>POST /api/2.0/mlflow/runs/create
    Notebook->>S3: Load training data<br/>AWS IAM Auth
    S3-->>Notebook: Dataset

    Note over Notebook: Training complete
    Notebook->>ModelRegistry: Register model<br/>POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models
    ModelRegistry-->>Notebook: Model ID

    Notebook->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>UI form submission
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>K8s API
    KServe->>Predictor: Deploy predictor<br/>Knative Service
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
    S3-->>Predictor: Model files

    Note over User,Gateway: Workflow 2: Inference Request
    User->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/mymodel:predict<br/>HTTPS, Bearer Token
    Gateway->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>mTLS, Service Identity
    Predictor->>ModelRegistry: Fetch model metadata (optional)<br/>gRPC/9090 mTLS
    ModelRegistry-->>Predictor: Model version info
    Predictor-->>Gateway: Inference result<br/>JSON response
    Gateway-->>User: 200 OK
